<h2>1. Introduction</h2>
<p>
  This document is a <strong>draft specification</strong> for the Web Everything injector syntax system.
  It formalizes the <code>provide</code>, <code>consume</code>, and <code>injector</code> block constructs
  explored in the <a href="/research/injector-syntax-proposals/">Provide/Consume/Injector Syntax Proposals</a>
  research, resolves open design questions, and defines normative desugaring from DSL to runtime API.
</p>

<h3>1.1 Conformance Tiers</h3>
<p>Every construct in this spec exists at three tiers. Only Tier 1 is normative; Tiers 2 and 3 are sugar that compiles down to Tier 1.</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Tier</th><th>Name</th><th>Requires</th><th>Status</th></tr>
  <tr>
    <td>1</td>
    <td><strong>Runtime API</strong></td>
    <td>Nothing — pure JS/TS</td>
    <td>Normative. Partially implemented.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>2</td>
    <td><strong>TypeScript API</strong></td>
    <td>Standard TypeScript compiler</td>
    <td>Typed wrappers over Tier 1. Designed but not yet implemented.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>3</td>
    <td><strong>DSL Syntax</strong></td>
    <td>Custom parser + transformer (esbuild plugin, Babel, or SWC)</td>
    <td>Aspirational. No tooling exists yet.</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p>
  <strong>Design principle:</strong> The DSL is syntactic sugar, not a separate system.
  If the transformer is unavailable, developers use the Runtime API directly with identical semantics.
  Every DSL construct has a normative desugaring to Tier 1.
</p>

<h3>1.2 Scope</h3>
<p>This spec covers:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Provide</strong> — registering providers on an injector</li>
  <li><strong>Consume</strong> — requesting providers from the injector chain</li>
  <li><strong>Injector blocks</strong> — declaring named injector scopes</li>
  <li><strong>import.injector</strong> — compile-time module scope reference</li>
  <li><strong>DOM integration</strong> — element-tree injection (plugged and unplugged)</li>
  <li><strong>Module integration</strong> — ES Module scope injection</li>
  <li><strong>Type system</strong> — TypeScript integration for typed providers</li>
  <li><strong>Tooling requirements</strong> — what each build tool needs</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>2. Syntax At a Glance</h2>
<p>
  The injector system has two independent dimensions:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>DSL vs Compiled</strong> — the DSL is syntactic sugar; a transpiler compiles it to standard Tier 1 runtime API calls.</li>
  <li><strong>Plugged vs Unplugged</strong> — how you access injectors from the DOM. Orthogonal to the DSL.</li>
</ul>

